        <headline>Flood Advisory issued August 18 at 6:22PM CDT until August 18 at 9:30PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.

* WHERE...A portion of northeast Illinois, including the following
counties, Cook, DuPage, Kane, Kendall and Will.

* WHEN...Until 930 PM CDT.

* IMPACTS...Flooding may occur in poor drainage and urban areas.
Underpasses may be flooded. Roads and streets may be flooded.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 620 PM CDT, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges
indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms extending central
Cook County westward to southern DuPage and northern Will
counties. Rainfall rates of 1-2 inches per hour continue. Up
to 2 inches of rain have fallen from these storms in southern
DuPage County.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Chicago, Aurora, Naperville, Elgin, Cicero, Hammond,
Evanston, Schaumburg, Bolingbrook, Skokie, Des Plaines,
Orland Park, Oak Lawn, Berwyn, Wheaton, Oak Park, Downers
Grove, Elmhurst, Lombard and Bartlett.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>A Flood Advisory means minor flooding along waterways and other poor
drainage areas is imminent or may already be occurring. Persons in
the advisory area should use caution and avoid flood waters.</instruction>
